   "source": "# PCE-weighted AI adoption and services inflation\n\nThis notebook builds a monthly scatterplot comparing PCE-weighted BTOS AI adoption with PCE-weighted non-annualized m/m inflation for a selected services mapping.\n\nMethod summary:\n\n1. Read Census BTOS sector-level AI adoption rates for the `Yes` response to question 7.\n2. Convert biweekly BTOS waves to months by assigning each wave to the month of the survey collection-period midpoint, then averaging waves within each month and sector.\n3. Map BTOS sectors to BEA NIPA underlying-detail PCE line items.\n4. For repeated PCE lines, aggregate mapped BTOS sectors to one line-level AI adoption rate. The default within-line allocation is equal sector weights, renormalized across sectors with valid BTOS observations in that month.\n5. Pull BEA Table 2.4.5U nominal PCE expenditures and Table 2.4.4U price indexes. PCE weights are lagged-period expenditure shares across the mapped line items.\n6. Compute non-annualized line-level m/m inflation from PCE price indexes, then aggregate inflation and AI adoption with the same lagged expenditure shares.\n\nSource note: the combined BTOS default uses the legacy AI question workbook while it has valid observations and the revised sector workbook for the valid post-break observations. Set `BTOS_SERIES_MODE` below if you want only one source.\n"
  },
